result.execSummary:
Jorge Zamudio Cervantes was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jorge Zamudio Cervantes was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Jorge Zamudio Cervantes

records.addlTxt: 1:06 p.m.  Commissioner Mike Korpela presiding, Marietta Appner, CR.  Matthew J. Tingstad appeared for the State of WI.  Def appeared in person, in custody.  Court calls case, cites appearances.  Fugitive crim complained file in the County re: pending Gogebic County case.  Court explains purpose of hearing.  Def states he understands.  Court proceeds with questions to def.  Def understands Gog. Co. charge.  DA hands copy of WI complaint and warrant to def.  Def does not wish to hire counsel at this time.  Def admits he is the person charged in MI.  Court explains bond amount in Gog. warrant.  Def understands his option to ask for Governors to get involved.  Court reads waiver of extradition from.  Def initials statements on form.  Commissioner Korpela certifies waiver of extradition in his presence and signs form.  Adj.  1:20 p.m.  Clerked by wmg.  Typed by klr.
